<div class="description"><span style="font-size: 150%;">Paladin Redirect Manager (PRM)</span> is Opencart module to manage redirections and keep track of 404 errors without requiring knowledge of Apache .htaccess files.
<br>
<span style="font-size: 140%;">What is a redirect?</span><br>
In its simplest form, a redirect is a way to take the user from one web-page to another. There are different Types of redirects, and each type can have different SEO implications.<br>
<br>
<span style="font-size: 150%;">You usually redirect a page for the following reasons:</span><span style="font-size: 130%;"><br>
- The URL is broken or it doesn't work<br>
- The webpage/site is no longer active<br>
- You have a new webpage/site that you want people to visit instead of the old one<br>
- You're A/B testing a new webpage in terms of design or functionality<br>
- You're fixing a webpage and you want to temporarily make a detour for your users for continual website experience<br>
- You want your users to make the best pancakes (just kidding!)</span><br>
<br>
<span style="font-size: 150%;">Features &amp; functions:</span><span style="font-size: 130%;"><br>
- Setting TIME ACTIVITY for Redirect Rules<br>
- <span style="color: red;">IMPORT urls</span> for Redirects from .csv file<br>
- EXPORT existing Redirect Rules to .csv file<br>
- Massive changing any redirect rules in ONE CLICK<br>
- Massive deleting any redirect rules in ONE CLICK<br>
- COUNTING incoming requests by hits, unique, users, bots<br>
- Manually add 301, 302, and 307 redirections for any pages<br>
- Searching and <span style="color: red;">SHOWING THE BROKEN LINKS</span> from Redirect Rules<br>
- PROCESSING FOR EMPTY URLs - redirect there to homepage or landing page<br>
- Flexible FILTERING SYSTEM by status, type, broken, empty and author for Redirect Rules<br>
- <span style="color: red;">404 ERROR MONITORING</span> - saves broken links in the Redirect Rules for redirecting them to correct pages<br>
- Inserting/editing/deleting <span style="color: red;">Redirect Rules in your .HTACCESS</span> file, as option, which you can use for improving website speed</span><br>

